## Why this replaces the dashboard 052845e case (D-12)
The dashboard-unbounded-dict fix `052845e` carries subject `fix(42): DR3m-01 ...` —
a live hit for the FAIL-CLOSED organic regex (DR = Deep-Review finding = vibe-check
found it), so the organic-only rule (D-12) categorically EXCLUDES it. This third
should-catch is a clean-organic, human/walkthrough-found bug fix mined from
seedsyncarr, keeping the should-catch set at the >=3 floor with zero circular
self-testing.

## What the reversed patch re-introduces
The fix (879266c) wrapped the percentage in `Math.min(100, ...)`. Extracted files
have local_size (unpacked) > remote_size (compressed archive), so
`Math.trunc(100 * local / remote)` exceeds 100 and rendered e.g. "199%" on the
dashboard, and mis-fired the `=== 100` success state. The reversed patch (this
.patch = `git diff 879266c 879266c^`, product file only) removes the clamp and its
explanatory comment, re-introducing the >100% bug. The commit body records it as a
"pre-existing defect surfaced during the v1.4.0 milestone-end walkthrough" (organic,
human-found — NOT a vibe-check DR finding). The patch is scoped to the PRODUCT file
only; the fix's test-vector file is fixture churn and is intentionally excluded so
the review surface is the real defect.

